        Label:
            text: "The Total Allowable Catch (TAC) for West Coast rock lobster (WCRL) is determined annually by the delegated authority, the Deputy Diretor General: Fisheries Management. The TAC is a global tonnage that is split between the commercial (offshore and nearshore), small-scale/interim relief and the recreational sectors. The recreational sector receives 4% of the global TAC which is managed through Total Applied Effort (TAE), granted as fishing days. Telephone surveys have been conducted to sample the number of fishers who utilise their permits. Estimating the number of fishers actively fishing at a maximum of 4 lobsters per day, the number of fishing days that will reach the TAC is calculated. The dates fall on weekends and close to public holidays and are chosen to accommodate the local fishers and holiday makers. The dates chosen coincide, where possible, as close to morning low tide as fishers prefer the low tide for optimal fishing and to easily reach the lobster that are further out."
            
